From dff90fab62390ae3dbdacbf5b246eee0c85e6c76 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Govinda Upadhyay <govinda.upadhyay@sipradi.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 05:23:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] feat: multi-sector + multi-location employee model
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SCHEMA
- Add emp_sectors(emp_id, sector_id, is_primary) junction table — same
  pattern as emp_roles. Replaces the single employees.dept string for
  sector assignment, allowing Sandeep to belong to Vehicle, WH Battery,
  and WH Lube simultaneously.
- Add emp_locations(emp_id, loc_id, is_primary) junction table so staff
  who work across branches (KTM HQ + Birgunj Border) are modelled correctly.
- Both tables created on first run and via migration on existing DBs.
- One-time back-fill: existing employees.dept values are migrated into
  emp_sectors automatically on startup — no data loss.

BACKEND
- enrich_emp() now returns sector_ids[] and loc_ids[] arrays on every
  employee object. Keeps employees.dept in sync with primary sector for
  backward compatibility (dc(), deptBadge, CSV exports all still work).
- employees POST + PUT: accept sector_ids[] and loc_ids[], save to
  junction tables, update dept to primary sector code.
- employees DELETE: cleans emp_sectors + emp_locations rows.
- NEW /api/analytics/by_sector: groups performance by emp_sectors
  junction (not emp.dept string), so multi-sector employees appear in
  every bucket they belong to.
- NEW /api/analytics/by_location: groups performance by emp_locations
  junction with fallback to sector-based location matching.

FRONTEND
- Employee form: Department single-select replaced with Sectors
  multi-select picker (first checked = primary, shown with Primary badge).
  Locations multi-select added below it. Same checkbox-list pattern as
  the existing role/MP/CP pickers.
- Employee card border colour and profile header now use primary sector
  colour instead of hard-coded dept string.
- Employee profile modal: shows all sector badges + all location badges
  instead of just the single dept badge.
- Perf entry form: Sector and Location dropdowns added. Auto-populated
  from the selected employee's primary sector/location when left blank,
  so existing workflows require zero extra clicks for single-sector staff.
- Reports → By Location & Sector: now calls real /api/analytics/by_sector
  and /api/analytics/by_location endpoints backed by junction tables,
  replacing the client-side emp.dept grouping that produced wrong buckets
  for multi-sector employees.
---
